# OpenIM module boundary

## Scope

- Business IM lives in `src/domains/openim/` and `im` PostgreSQL schema.
- Message bodies stay in **OpenIM**; PG holds mappings, participants, snapshots, attachments metadata.
- **Do not** copy full message history into PG.

## API channels (by initiating client)

| Prefix | Client |
|--------|--------|
| `/api/openim/customer-merchant/*` | WeChat / Site (JWT) |
| `/api/admin/openim/customer-merchant/*` | CMS merchant staff |
| `/api/openim/merchant-push/*` | Customer read-only (P1) |
| `/api/admin/openim/merchant-push/*` | Merchant send (P1, `MERCHANT_PUSH` feature) |

`customer_merchant` is bidirectional and **not** gated by `MERCHANT_PUSH`. `merchant_push` sets `allow_customer_send = false`.

## S3

- Chat attachments: `im/conversations/{conversationId}/attachments/{yyyy}/{mm}/{fileId}.ext`
- Use `openimAttachmentS3Util` — **not** `s3UploadManager` merchant/user prefixes.

## Enums / types

- Shared contracts: `xituan_codebase/typing_entity/openim-chat.enum.ts`, `typing_api/openim-chat.type.ts`
- Never hardcode conversation type strings; use `epOpenimConversationType` / `epOpenimChannel`.

## Migrations

- New SQL only under `xituan_backend/migrations/` (next index).
- Do not edit `migrations_stable/` or run SQL without explicit permission.
